CFR International SpA: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 9:40 AM ET
Pharmaceuticals

Company Overview of CFR International SpA



Snapshot People




Company Overview
CFR International SpA, through its subsidiaries, manufactures and develops pharmaceutical preparations. It operates in Latin America through 4 segments; specialty pharma (medication for chronic, semi-chronic and acute diseases), complex therapeutics (medications aimed at diseases treated in complex treatment centers and institutions), health and wellness (over-the-counter medications, nutrition, dermocare, diet supplements and homeopathic medications), and veterinary medications. The company executed an agreement with Universidad de Chile for the project “Fondef” focused on the development of gene therapy for the treatment of alcoholism. The company was incorporated in 2010 and is based in S...
CFR International SpA, through its subsidiaries, manufactures and develops pharmaceutical preparations. It operates in Latin America through 4 segments; specialty pharma (medication for chronic, semi-chronic and acute diseases), complex therapeutics (medications aimed at diseases treated in complex treatment centers and institutions), health and wellness (over-the-counter medications, nutrition, dermocare, diet supplements and homeopathic medications), and veterinary medications. The company executed an agreement with Universidad de Chile for the project “Fondef” focused on the development of gene therapy for the treatment of alcoholism. The company was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Santiago, Chile. CFR International SpA operates as a subsidiary of CFR Pharmaceuticals S.A.
Detailed Description


